Docs.summary: This property is used to associate an on-premises Active Directory user account to their Azure AD user object. MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.Toolkit.Services.MicrosoftGraph.MicrosoftGraphUserFields PasswordPolicies = int32(25)
PasswordPolicies = 25

Docs.summary: Specifies password policies for the user. This value is an enumeration with one possible value being “DisableStrongPassword”, which allows weaker passwords than the default policy to be specified. “DisablePasswordExpiration” can also be specified. The two may be specified together; for example: 'DisablePasswordExpiration, DisableStrongPassword'.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.Toolkit.Services.MicrosoftGraph.MicrosoftGraphUserFields PasswordProfile = int32(26)
PasswordProfile = 26

Docs.summary: Specifies the password profile for the user. The profile contains the user’s password. This property is required when a user is created. The password in the profile must satisfy minimum requirements as specified by the passwordPolicies property. By default, a strong password is required.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.Toolkit.Services.MicrosoftGraph.MicrosoftGraphUserFields UserPrincipalName = int32(39)
UserPrincipalName = 39

Docs.summary: The user principal name (UPN) of the user. The UPN is an Internet-style login name for the user based on the Internet standard RFC 822. By convention, this should map to the user's email name. The general format is alias@domain, where domain must be present in the tenant’s collection of verified domains. This property is required when a user is created. The verified domains for the tenant can be accessed from the verifiedDomains property of organization.
